gomodel:SYNGO_2436  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"The Arp2/3 complex regulates the formation of dendritic spines and synapses in hippocampal neurons\"\n- Literal: \"Higher magnification images showed that Arp3 puncta were in close apposition to SV2 clusters and completely merged with PSD-95 puncta, indicating that Arp3, like N-WASP, is enriched on the postsynaptic side of excitatory synapses (Fig. 6A).\". Experimental description: Cell Culture and Transfection-Hippocampal low density cultures were prepared as described previously (18). Reference 18 is entitled: Rat Hippocampal Neurons in Low-density Culture (Banker, G., and Goslin, K., eds) pp. 339-370, MIT Press, Cambridge, MA" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2436" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

